The paper introduces a new type of graphical model for expressing joint cumulative distributions and describes a message-passing algorithm for computing conditional cumulative distributions. This work is relevant to machine learning and statistical inference, which suggests that the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
